</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Traffic in Athens came to a standstill yesterday when striking public
transport workers marched in protest against the sacking of 1,200 people by
the state bus company, Reuter reports from Athens.
Buses disappeared from the Greek capital and commuters who used cars or
taxis were trapped in huge jams.
The union representing the bus workers said its 6,000 members would continue
to strike until the conservative government rescinded the sackings, aimed at
