FT  23 JUL 92 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MEXICO'S stock market ended 2 per cent weaker yesterday, dragged down by a
4.1 per cent drop in Cemex 'B' shares and a decline of 2 per cent for
Telmex, the respective cement and telephone companies.
Cemex CPO shares - those held in a special trust for foreign investors -
were down 10 per cent at one point, as Morgan Stanley, previously a staunch
Cemex supporter, failed to endorse the company in a report.
Foreign investors have reacted negatively to Cemex's recent decision to buy
Spain's two largest cement companies, Sanson and Valenciana.
