<TEXT>
A Chip in the Sugar (BBC2 at 9.30pm) is exquisite and unmissable. In this
second repeat of the famous Talking Head monologues by Alan Bennett, the
author himself stars as the repressed, middle-aged son of a fearsome mother.
El Caudillo was born a century ago this year. Franco: Behind the Myth (BBC1
at 10.20pm), is billed as a documentary which unearths the truth about a
ruler whom modern, Olympic-hosting Spain, has consigned to oblivion. Surely
an exaggeration, but nevertheless, producer Anthony Geffen has a good
track-record with profiles of dictators,. An 'exclusive' interview with his
confessor sounds promising.
