FT  23 JUL 92 / Freeze on sale of County Hall
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government said last night that it was freezing the sale of County Hall,
former headquarters of the Greater London Council, until the end of this
month.
Mr Michael Howard, environment secretary, told the London Residuary Body,
which controls the site, to suspend action on sale until July 31 to allow
the London School of Economics a fair chance to submit a bid for the
premises.
The department said it had received assurances from the director of the LSE
that the school could submit a bid by that date.
Mr Howard said, however, that if no bid was forthcoming by the deadline, the
LRB would be free to act as it sees fit in pursuit of its statutory
responsibilities.
