<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUL 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Australian wool auctions are resumed next week. The market during the recess
has been nominally static, but with dollar currencies weakening for most of
the month, price ideas in most major consuming countries have eased. The
Australian view is not by any means bearish, however, and some European
traders consider that prices could possibly rise to begin with. Calculations
further ahead are influenced by the four million bale stockpile, which has
to be disposed of at some stage, by recession and by the inability of the
old Soviet countries to buy.
