resources. The cost reduction programme would continue, the company said.
Earnings per share improved to 7.6p (6p) and the proposed final dividend of
1.6p lifts the total to 2.7p (2.1p).
For the remainder of 1992 advertising revenues were expected to achieve at
best marginal growth, directors said. They were confident, however, that
their arrangement in the north for Granada to market and sell its airtime
would be beneficial.
Border has holdings in Radio Borders and South-West Sound in Scotland and
has recently acquired a 30 per cent holding in Morecambe Bay Radio. It is
also part of a consortium bidding for the Carlisle radio franchise.
