FT  23 JUL 92 / Tourism blow
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE WELSH holiday industry suffered a 4 per cent fall in income last year,
according to the Welsh Tourist Board. A survey of hotels showed bed
occupancy averaging 37 per cent, its lowest level for eight years.
Those hotels geared to the business and conference trade, especially in
south Wales, were suffering worst.
