<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUL 92 / World Trade News: Nike loses Olympic race
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER BRUCE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Nike International, the US sporting clothes and footwear group, yesterday
lost a race to have a ban on the sale and marketing of its clothing in Spain
lifted before the start of the Olympic Games in Barcelona on Saturday,
writes Peter Bruce in Madrid.
Spain's constitutional court rejected a second appeal by Nike in favour of
claims by a Catalan company that it owns the Nike trademark in Spain. The
decision sets the stage for a potentially embarrassing inaugural ceremony as
it means the Spanish claimant could ask police to stop the US athletic team,
sponsored by Nike, entering the Olympic stadium wearing the Nike (US) logo.
</TEXT>
